ing: 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley, or to taste
des: "Chickpea spread. We often replace a portion of the chickpeas with cooked edamame. This gives the hummus a nice green tint and sweetens it a very small amount."
ins: Combine chickpeas, tahini, water, lemon juice, garlic, cumin, and salt in food processor or blender; puree until smooth. Transfer hummus to a flat dish. Sprinkle parsley over the hummus to serve.
